PR #7 review feedback
- backend/routers/chat: tighten _model_is_pulled so it equates a base
  name with its :latest tag (per Ollama's default behavior) but keeps
  size/version variants distinct. 'llama3:8b' no longer masks a missing
  'llama3:70b'.
- frontend/app: show the 'Refresh model list' button whenever pulled is
  empty, regardless of pullable status â€” students can now recover from
  an empty initial load.
image rendering ([GÃ–RSEL: ...] cite was producing a broken icon)
- The previous implementation passed BACKEND_URL/ingest/image to
  st.image(), which made the *browser* fetch the URL. That failed
  because the URL points at a Docker-network hostname the browser
  cannot resolve, and even on localhost it would 401 without the
  Authorization header. fetch_image_bytes now downloads the image via
  Python with the bearer token and hands the bytes to st.image.
- backend/routers/ingest: relax /ingest/image dependency from
  require_instructor to get_current_user so students can also view
  cited figures. Path-traversal guard intact.
duplicate detection visibility
- services/ingestion: emit a final `INGESTION_RESULT:<json>` line with
  the per-file summary; also include metadata-hash matches in the local
  dedup check (catches same paper saved with cosmetic differences in
  the first pages but identical title/author).
- backend/routers/ingest: parse the INGESTION_RESULT line from the
  subprocess stdout and return it. Previously the endpoint always
  returned processed=0/duplicates=0, hiding the dedup outcome.
- frontend/app: after ingest, show processed/duplicates/errors counts
  and expand a "Duplicate files skipped" list with the reason
  ('identical file', 'same content', 'same title/author'). Users now
  see when a re-uploaded book was rejected as a duplicate.
